'''''Micro Golf''''' is a [[sports video game]] published in 1981 by [[Creative Computing Software]] for the [[Apple II]].

==Gameplay==
''Micro Golf'' is a game in which 1 to 4 players play miniature golf.<ref name="CGW5"/>

==Reception==
Bob Boyd reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "One of the best features of this game is that it is not limited to a special age or interest group. It is great for showing people your computer because there aren't hefty rules to learn, you can just start playing, and it is still very challenging for everyone."<ref name="CGW5">{{cite magazine |last=Boyd |first=Bob |title=Micro - Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=Julyâ€“August 1982 |volume=1 |issue=5 |pages=36}}</ref>

